I need to identify two key line items from this income statement:
1. The value of income arising from the entity's core operating activities
2. The carrying amount of inventories sold during the reporting period

Looking at the income statement:
- The "Main Business Revenue" (863371.65) represents the income from core operating activities
- The "Cost of Goods Sold" (562950.00) represents the carrying amount of inventories sold

These are the standard line items that correspond to the requested information. The Main Business Revenue shows what the company earned from its primary business operations, while Cost of Goods Sold shows the cost of inventory that was sold to generate that revenue.
